    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-06-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">E. Alexander</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Uhl</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received July 17.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 37.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * The draft of a trade-mark convention has
                    been submitted to the minister for foreign affairs, who is now considering the
                    matter. In May I had several conferences with him on this subject. It is
                    probable that the convention can be concluded at once.</p>
                <p>I am translating the laws of Greece relating to trademarks, and will send you the
                    translation as soon as possible.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Alexander.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
